  <section class='learn_header'>
    <h1>How to Take CBD and Adjust the Dose</h1>
    <img src='/logo-farm-doc-reverse.png' class='small center' />
    <p>If your patient has not used CBD before, Table 1 is a guide for the typical dose range people use, depending on what they are using it for.  They should use the lowest dose that is effective for them.</p>
    <p>See Tables 2 and 3 for determining their optimal dose.<sup>*</sup></p>
  </section>
  <p>* If they are using CBD for general health, without any specific symptoms, there is no reason to adjust the dose up.</p>
  <section>
    <h2>Typical Dose Based on Reason for Taking CBD</h2>
    <table class='question-table'>
      <caption>Table 1.  Typical Dose</caption>
      <tr><th>Reason for trying CBD</th><th>Recommended Product</th><th>Typical Dose</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Intermittent joint pain</td><td>Topical Salve</td><td>1 or 2% salve 1-2 times/day, as needed</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Daily joint pain</td><td>Sublingual Oil</td><td>20-30 mg/day</td></tr>
