  <section>
    <h2>Determining the Optimal Dose</h2>
    <p>The amount of CBD a person requires to get the desired benefit varies from person to person, due to genetic differences.  <em>If they have not taken CBD before, it is recommended they start at 10 mg CBD/day and increase weekly until they get the desired effect.</em></p>
    <p><em>Formulations of CBD will vary between producers.</em>  Patients should select a product that is in the range of 25-35 mg/ml and adjust the number of sprays or drops to approximate the doses listed in the table below.</p>
    <p class='center-quote'>The following tables are based on a sublingual oil formulation that contains 30 mg CBD/ml.</p>
    <p>They can find a product that contains 30 mg/ml at <a href='https://shop.ravenridgefamilyfarm.com'>shop.ravenridgefamilyfarm.com</a>.</p>
    <hr />
    <h3>Sublingual Spray:</h3>
    <p>It can take 2-3 days to know if the dose produces the desired effect.</p>
    <ul class='padded-list'>
      <li>Start by using 2 sprays (10mg)/day, under the tongue or on inside of cheeks, either as a single dose in the AM or PM, or half the dose AM and PM.</li>
      <li>If they are not getting the desired effect, increase each week by 2 sprays (10mg)/day and continue increasing until it is effective.</li>
    </ul>
    <img src='/use_sublingual.png' class='center medium' alt='To use sublingual oil, spray on the inside of the cheek or place drops under the tongue.' />
    <table class='product-table'>
      <caption>Table 2. Dosage Chart for 900 mg Bottle, Sprayer (30 mg/ml daily dose)</caption>
      <tr><th># of Sprays</th><th>CBD Dose in mg</th></tr>
      <tr><td>8</td><td>40 mg</td></tr>
      <tr><td>6</td><td>30 mg</td></tr>
      <tr><td>4</td><td>20 mg</td></tr>
      <tr><td>2</td><td>10 mg</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p><strong>*If no benefit after 2 weeks at 40 mg (8 sprays)/day, CBD should be discontinued, as it is unlikely to be effective for them.</strong></p>
    <hr />
    <h3>Sublingual Drops:</h3>
    <p>They should place drops under the tongue. Hold under tongue for 30 seconds before swallowing.</p>
    <p>It can take 2-3 days to know if the dose produces the desired effect.</p>
    <ul class='padded-list'>
      <li>Start by using 0.3 ml (10mg)/day, either as a single dose in the AM or PM, or half the dose AM and PM.</li>
      <li>If they are not getting the desired effect,  increase each week by 0.3 ml (10 mg)/day and continue increasing until it is effective, which will be their optimal dose.</li>
    </ul>
    <table class='product-table'>
      <caption>Table 3. Dosage Chart for 900 mg Bottle, Dropper</caption>
      <tr><th>Amount (approximate) in mls</th><th>CBD Dose in mg</th></tr>
      <tr><td>1.3</td><td>40 mg</td></tr>
      <tr><td>1.0</td><td>30 mg</td></tr>
      <tr><td>0.7</td><td>20 mg</td></tr>
      <tr><td>0.3</td><td>10 mg</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p><strong>*If no benefit after 2 weeks at 40 mg (1.3ml)/day, CBD should be discontinued, as it is unlikely to be effective for them.</strong></p>
    <hr />
    <h3>CBD Salve or Cream:</h3>
    <p><strong>The “fingertip rule” for applying topical salve or cream</strong></p>
    <img src='/use_salve.png' class='center small' alt='Using salve following the fingertip rule is as easy as it sounds. Use a dollop on your fingertip for each affected area.'/>
    <p>They should start with the 1% strength.</p>
    <p>Apply a fingertip worth to each body area being treated.  Rub in for 15-30 seconds.</p>
    <p>Apply 1-2 times daily, as needed.</p>
    <p>If they get no benefit after using 5-7 days increase to 2% strength.  If no benefit after using the 2% strength 2 times/day they are unlikely to get the desired benefit from topical application.</p>
    {{>fda_approved}}
